One of the most interesting old askreddit threads I remember was one about people with parents who were intellectually disabled. Like sometimes a guy with some form of autism or mental retardation and a female with severe learning disability end up having normal children together

The stories were really interesting, most of them ended up basically being raised by their neighbors if there were no grandparents involved, many parents were too dysfunctional to take them to the doctor when they were sick because they couldn't figure out how buses worked etc...

I think most said they intellectually outgrew their parents by age 11-12 or so, often no one in the house was able to cook any food, the place was horribly filthy, etc. Being on reddit itself is a powerful selection tool ofc. but for most of the ppl in the thread it worked out ok
Well most of them didnt have internet until they moved out I assume
